ions\\\": 7,\\n10468:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 0,\\n10486:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10526:      \\\"iterations\\\": 1,\\n10528:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 104,\\n10546:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success_with_intervention\\\",\\n10596:      \\\"iterations\\\": 23,\\n10598:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 640,\\n10616:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10661:      \\\"iterations\\\": 23,\\n10663:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 938,\\n10681:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10715:      \\\"iterations\\\": 5,\\n10717:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 558,\\n10735:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10775:      \\\"iterations\\\": 3,\\n10777:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 70,\\n10795:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10835:      \\\"iterations\\\": 6,\\n10837:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 360,\\n10855:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10894:      \\\"analysis_markdown\\\": \\\"# Post-generation intervention report\\\\n\\\\nLibrary: org.jboss.classfilewriter:jboss-classfilewriter:1.2.4.Final\\\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\\\n\\\\n## Summary\\\\n\\\\nThe post-generation failure was caused by two non-metadata native-image limitations in generated tests, not by additional missing reachability metadata.\\\\n\\\\nThe Codex metadata-fix log shows that Codex already added reflection metadata for the exercised `org.jboss.classfilewriter` paths, and that this was enough to make the metadata-driven coverage tests pass. The remaining failures came from tests that attempt runtime class definition or depend on JDK internals that are not available on this GraalVM/JDK 25 setup.\\\\n\\\\nI removed the generated failing tests:\\\\n\\\\n- `tests/src/org.jboss.classfilewriter/jboss-classfilewriter/1.2.4.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_classfilewriter/jboss_classfilewriter/AnnotationBuilderTest.java`\\\\n- `tests/src/org.jboss.classfilewriter/jboss-classfilewriter/1.2.4.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_classfilewriter/jboss_classfilewriter/DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`\\\\n\\\\nAfter removing those non-metadata tests, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.classfilewriter:jboss-classfilewriter:1.2.4.Final --stacktrace` passed.\\\\n\\\\n## Failure-by-failure root cause\\\\n\\\\n### 1. `AnnotationBuilderTest.copiesRuntimeVisibleAnnotationsFromJavaAnnotationInstances()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: non-metadata native-image limitation.\\\\n\\\\nThis test generates bytecode and then calls a custom class loader method that ultimately invokes `ClassLoader#defineClass(...)` at runtime for `GeneratedAnnotationBuilderCoverage...`.\\\\n\\\\nThe native run failed with `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.UnsupportedFeatureError: Classes cannot be defined at runtime by default when using ahead-of-time Native Image compilation`.\\\\n\\\\nThat is not a missing-registration error and not a missing metadata problem. The failure is caused by runtime class definition being unsupported by default in Native Image.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `AnnotationBuilderTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 2. `DefaultClassFactoryTest.invokesMethodInvokeLineUsingSyntheticDefaultClassFactoryWithoutProtectionDomain()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: non-metadata JDK/platform incompatibility.\\\\n\\\\nThis test initializes `org.jboss.classfilewriter.DefaultClassFactory`, whose implementation reflectively looks up the internal field `AccessibleObject.override`. On this GraalVM/JDK 25 environment, that field is not present, so initialization fails with a synthesized `NoSuchFieldException: override`.\\\\n\\\\nThis is not a reachability metadata issue. Metadata cannot restore a removed or unavailable JDK internal field.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 3. `DefaultClassFactoryTest.definesClassThroughDefaultFactoryUsingProvidedClassLoaderAndProtectionDomain()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: same non-metadata JDK/platform incompatibility as above.\\\\n\\\\nThis test is also blocked by `DefaultClassFactory` initialization against the missing `override` field. The assertion mismatch in the failure excerpt is downstream from that initialization problem and does not indicate missing metadata.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n### 4. `DefaultClassFactoryTest.invokesMethodInvokeLineUsingSyntheticDefaultClassFactoryWithProtectionDomain()`\\\\n\\\\nRoot cause: same non-metadata JDK/platform incompatibility as above.\\\\n\\\\nBecause `DefaultClassFactory` cannot initialize successfully, the test fails with `NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class org.jboss.classfilewriter.DefaultClassFactory`.\\\\n\\\\nAgain, this is not a metadata gap; it is a consequence of the unavailable JDK internal field relied on by the library code path.\\\\n\\\\nAction taken: removed the generated test file `DefaultClassFactoryTest.java`.\\\\n\\\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\\\n\\\\nThe remaining generated support is still useful and should be kept because it exercises library behavior that does work under Native Image once the generated metadata is present.\\\\n\\\\nThe surviving tests still cover:\\\\n\\\\n- class structure and bytecode generation\\\\n- switch generation and exception-handler bytecode\\\\n- runtime-visible annotation writing for class, field, method, and parameter targets\\\\n- generic signatures and checked exceptions\\\\n- `CodeAttribute` frame merging using loaded concrete collection types\\\\n\\\\nThose tests all passed after removing the unrelated native-image/JDK-internal cases, so the generated support is not scaffold-only and should not be discarded just because a few tests targeted unsupported runtime class-definition behavior.\\\\n\\\\n## Metadata status\\\\n\\\\nNo additional metadata-only failure remained in the provided failure set.\\\\n\\\\nThe Codex log indicates the metadata fix progressed far enough to resolve the metadata-driven failures that were actually fixable here. The remaining failing tests were blocked by:\\\\n\\\\n- Native Image runtime class-definition restrictions\\\\n- reliance on the missing JDK internal field `override`\\\\n\\\\nBecause those are not metadata issues, the correct intervention was to remove the generated tests that depended on those unsupported behaviors rather than remove the rest of the generated support or attempt further metadata edits.\\\"\\n10900:      \\\"iterations\\\": 8,\\n10902:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 776,\\n10920:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10934:      \\\"iterations\\\": 3,\\n10936:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 425,\\n10954:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n10988:      \\\"iterations\\\": 4,\\n10990:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 590,\\n11008:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11048:      \\\"iterations\\\": 1,\\n11050:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 24,\\n11066:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11071:      \\\"iterations\\\": 14,\\n11073:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 652,\\n11091:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success_with_intervention\\\",\\n11141:      \\\"iterations\\\": 10,\\n11143:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 718,\\n11161:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success_with_intervention\\\",\\n11211:      \\\"iterations\\\": 16,\\n11213:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 704,\\n11231:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success_with_intervention\\\",\\n11276:      \\\"iterations\\\": 7,\\n11278:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 316,\\n11296:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11336:      \\\"iterations\\\": 2,\\n11338:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 387,\\n11352:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11356:      \\\"iterations\\\": 8,\\n11358:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 220,\\n11376:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11421:      \\\"iterations\\\": 7,\\n11423:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 355,\\n11441:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11455:      \\\"iterations\\\": 4,\\n11457:      \\\"generated_loc\\\": 256,\\n11475:    \\\"status\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n11489:      \\\"iterations\\\": 4,\\n11491:      \\\"generated_