_Yrf8nmQu6XNCvbbmkrLN9jXH|fc_01054334ed3e0ec40169f15c56a7708191ae465dde8e5deec7 name=read status=success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  # Developing the Repository Infrastructure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  This document summarizes those commands that you need to perform development tasks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  This repo is developed with IntelliJ. To initialize use:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  intellij-idea-community ./\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  Always use the Gradle wrapper from the repository root:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - Unix: `./gradlew <task> [options]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - Windows: `gradlew.bat <task> [options]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  Prerequisites for most commands:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - `JAVA_HOME` should be set to JDK 21 or later. GraalVM is recommended to match CI.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - Docker (required for pulling/using allowed images during tests). Needs to work without `sudo`: `sudo usermod -aG docker $USER` and reboot.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  - [`grype`](https://github.com/anchore/grype) version `0.104.0` for scanning docker images:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      curl -sSfL https://get.anchore.io/grype/v0.104.0/install.sh | sudo sh -s -- -b /usr/local/bin\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  Tip: When debugging locally, add `--stacktrace` for better error output.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ### End-to-end testing before the commit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ./gradlew testAllInfra --stacktrace\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  To run the same coverage with future defaults enabled:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew testAllInfra --stacktrace\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ### Style and formatting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  1. To check style use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew checkstyle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     This will run Checkstyle using `gradle/checkstyle.xml`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  2. Spotless Verifies formatting (used in release workflow prior to packaging):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ./gradlew spotlessCheck\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  3. Auto-fix license headers and formatting locally:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew spotlessApply\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     Spotless enforces the CC0 license header on Java, Groovy, Gradle build scripts, and shell scripts. The metadata/** directory is excluded from header checks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ### Testing one library locally\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  For a single coordinate, CI runs three steps in this order:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  1. Pull Docker images:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  2. Validate index.json file integrity and schemas:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ./gradlew validateIndexFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  2. Validate metadata:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  3. Then run tests:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n     ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  To run the same coordinate with future defaults enabled:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ### Testing libraries in bulk\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  To exercise many tests at once, you can target all coordinates or a slice of the test space via the N/M shard syntax.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  All coordinates:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  1. Test the whole repo:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=all\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=all\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=all\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  2. Splitting the tests in batches (e.g., batch 1 of 16):\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=1/16\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=1/16\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=1/16\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ### Listing available coordinates\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  To print all testable GAV coordinates while honoring the same -Pcoordinates filter semantics used by the harness:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=all\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=1/16\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact -PstrictCoordinates=true\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  In GitHub Actions, this task also writes a space-separated list to the GITHUB_OUTPUT key \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coordinates\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  With `-PstrictCoordinates=true`, `listCoordinates` uses strict matching (`getMatchingCoordinatesStrict`) while keeping the same output format.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  ### Generating dependency graphs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  \\\